New Hardee is a no-frill carry out Chinese restaurant in Bed-Stuy. Their menu is mostly traditional chinese restaurant food, with the addition of some foods to cater to the large hispanic and black community surrounding. There is a bench inside the waiting room. They have a sliding plexi/glass door separating the cooking/serving area from the waiting room. My experience was that they are not that friendly, although a flatmate of mine was hit on by one of the girls working the counter. Food takes about 15 minutes from order placed to in-your-hands, so plan accordingly, and potentially call ahead or place an order on Grubhub. This is very basic food. I have a reasonable skill in cooking, and can confidently say that if I had a recipe, I could make this food better than they could. This is especially true for their mediocre dumplings, which are far over priced for the doughy tasteless mess you receive. They don't seem too open to substitutions, and are cash only (ATM within) On occasion I will dine from this restaurant, but only due to convenient location, and lack of many other options in the neighborhood.
